### Wishlist API — example requests
# Works with the VS Code "REST Client" extension and the JetBrains HTTP client.
# Send the requests top-to-bottom: `login` captures a token that the wishlist
# requests reuse via {{login.response.body.$.data.token}}.
#
# Docker:  http://localhost:8080/api      Local: http://127.0.0.1:8000/api

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080/api
@email = ada@example.com
@password = password123

### Register (public) -> 201, returns a token
# @name register
POST {{baseUrl}}/register
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "name": "Ada Lovelace",
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}",
  "password_confirmation": "{{password}}"
}

### Login (public) -> 200, returns a token
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/login
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### Token captured from the login response, reused below.
@token = {{login.response.body.$.data.token}}

### List products (public, no token) -> 200
GET {{baseUrl}}/products
Accept: application/json

### Add a product to my wishlist -> 201
POST {{baseUrl}}/wishlist
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "product_id": 1
}

### Get my wishlist -> 200 (only my items, product eager-loaded)
GET {{baseUrl}}/wishlist
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Add the same product again -> 409 (atomic duplicate prevention)
POST {{baseUrl}}/wishlist
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "product_id": 1
}

### Add an invalid product -> 422 (validation: exists:products,id)
POST {{baseUrl}}/wishlist
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "product_id": 999999
}

### Remove the product from my wishlist -> 200
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/wishlist/1
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Remove it again -> 404 (generic "Resource not found.", no existence leak)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/wishlist/1
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Wishlist without a token -> 401 ("Unauthenticated.")
GET {{baseUrl}}/wishlist
Accept: application/json

### Logout -> 200, revokes the current token (reusing it afterwards -> 401)
POST {{baseUrl}}/logout
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
